rl":"/docs/components/layout/box#elevation","content":"The elevation prop adds visual depth using box-shadow."},"1469":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-25","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rounding","content":"The rounding prop sets border-radius. Use `full` for fully rounded corners."},"1470":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-26","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"Box is fully polymorphic - the `as` prop allows rendering as any HTML element or custom component while preserving type-safe props."},"1471":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-27","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**HTML Elements:** When using `as=\"button\"`, TypeScript enforces button-specific props like `type`, `disabled`, and `onClick`."},"1472":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-28","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Custom Components:** When using `as={MyComponent}`, Box accepts that component's props. If there's a prop name conflict, Box's props take priority."},"1473":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-29","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Typed Refs:** Refs are correctly typed based on the `as` value - `useRef<HTMLButtonElement>` works with `as=\"button\"`."},"1474":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-30","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Self-alignment props allow Box to position itself within flex or grid containers."},"1475":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-31","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"Box uses CSS logical properties (`padding-inline-start`, `padding-block-end`, etc.) which automatically adapt to RTL layouts. No additional configuration is needed."},"1476":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-32","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"All spacing, elevation, and rounding values are derived from the theme. If no theme is provided, default values are used. This ensures consistency across the design system."},"1477":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"page","content":"Grid","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid"},"1478":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid","content":"Two-dimensional CSS Grid layout component for complex grid-based layouts with rows and columns"},"1479":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#installation","content":"Installation"},"1480":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-2","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#props","content":"Props"},"1481":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-3","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#scale-sizes","content":"Scale Sizes"},"1482":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-4","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#examples","content":"Examples"},"1483":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-5","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#default","content":"Default"},"1484":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-6","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#columns","content":"Columns"},"1485":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-7","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#gap","content":"Gap"},"1486":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-8","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#named-areas","content":"Named Areas"},"1487":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-9","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#responsive-grid","content":"Responsive Grid"},"1488":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-10","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#alignment","content":"Alignment"},"1489":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-11","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#form-layout","content":"Form Layout"},"1490":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-12","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#rtl-support","content":"RTL Support"},"1491":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-13","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#grid-vs-flex","content":"Grid vs Flex"},"1492":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-14","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid","content":"Grid is a two-dimensional CSS Grid layout component for complex grid-based layouts. It extends `Box`, inheriting all Box capabilities (padding, elevation, rounding, self-alignment, and polymorphic `as` prop)."},"1493":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-15","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid","content":"**Use Grid when**: You need explicit two-dimensional layouts with rows and columns, named grid areas, or responsive auto-fill patterns."},"1494":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-16","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#props","content":"The `Grid` component accepts the following props:"},"1495":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-17","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#scale-sizes","content":"We use the same scale sizes as the `Box` component. For more information, see the **Box component documentation**."},"1496":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-18","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#default","content":"Basic 3-column grid layout with gap."},"1497":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-19","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#columns","content":"The `columns` prop defines grid column tracks using CSS grid-template-columns syntax."},"1498":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-20","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#gap","content":"The `gap` prop controls spacing between grid cells. Use `rowGap` and `columnGap` for independent control."},"1499":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-21","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#named-areas","content":"Use `areas` to define named grid regions. Children use `gridArea` prop for placement."},"1500":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-22","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#responsive-grid","content":"Use CSS `auto-fill` and `minmax()` for responsive column counts without media queries."},"1501":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-23","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#alignm